The Oyo state governor, Engr. Seyi Makinde has disclosed the reasons behind the visit of the G-5 members of the opposition Peoples Democratic Party, PDP to President Bola Tinubu at the Presidential Villa, Abuja on Thursday. The group consists of immediate past governors which include Nyesom Wike (Rivers) Samuel Ortom (Benue) Okezie Ikpeazu(Abia) Ifeanyi Uguwanyi(Enugu) and incumbent Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State. After the meeting, Makinde told the State House Press Correspondents the essence of the visit was hinged on building the nation. “Well, nation-building is a very difficult task. You have to keep evaluating, you know what you’re doing, where you’re going? So, we have to keep seeing the President you know, to let them know what is happening. “And for the G-5, the integrity group, we also came to let the President know what we stood for. Fairness, justice, and equity.